## ‚úÖ what i did  
-clicked start
-opened the terminal
-ran: 'tmux'
-pressed: 'Ctrl+b+c'
-ran: 'grep -r accept /usr/include'
found out the accept syscall number is 43
-pressed: 'Ctrl+b+p'
-ran: 'vim bro.s'
-typed: '.intel_syntax noprefix'
        '.global _start'
        '_start:'
        'mov rax, 41'
        'mov rdi, 2'
        'mov rsi, 1'
        'mov rdx, 0'
        'syscall'
        'mov r10, rax'
        'sub rsp, 16'
        'mov r11, 0x2'
        'mov [rsp], r11w'
        'mov r11, 0x5000'
        'mov [rsp+2], r11w'
        'mov r11, 0x00000000'
        'mov [rsp+4], r11d'
        'mov r11, 0'
        'mov [rsp+8], r11d'
        'mov rax, 49'
        'mov rdi, r10'
        'mov rsi, rsp'
        'mov rdx, 16'
        'syscall'
        'mov rax, 50'
        'mov rdi, r10'
        'mov rsi, 0'
        'syscall'
        'mov rax, 43'
        'mov rdi, r10'
        'mov rsi, 0'
        'mov rdx, 0'
        'syscall'
        'mov rax, 60'
        'mov rdi, 0'
        'syscall'
-ran: 'as -o bro.o bro.s'
-ran: 'ld -o bro bro.o'
-flag popped out

## üßëüèæ‚Äçüè´ what this challenge teaches u
accept syscall number is 43 and it takes 3 arguments:
rdi -> socket file descriptor
rsi -> pointer to a struct w/ details of the client. u can use NULL to avoid details
rdx -> struct's lenght. set to NULL if rsi is NULL
accept gives back a file descriptor in which there is an active communication between the server and the client

